<!-- ===== CHAPTER 3: SYSTEM DESIGN ===== -->
<div class="page-break">
  <h1>CHAPTER 3<br/>SYSTEM DESIGN</h1>

  <h2>3.1 System Architecture</h2>

  <h3>3.1.1 Overview</h3>
  <p>Study Share follows a three-tier client-server architecture deployed as separate frontend and backend services, communicating over REST APIs. The architecture is designed for separation of concerns, horizontal scalability, and fault isolation between components.</p>

  <h3>3.1.2 Architectural Tiers</h3>

  <h4>Tier 1 – Presentation Layer (Frontend)</h4>
  <p>The frontend is built with Next.js 16.2 running on React 19, deployed as a server-side rendered (SSR) and client-side hybrid application. Next.js's App Router handles routing with layouts, providing persistent UI shells (sidebar, navigation) across page transitions. Tailwind CSS 4 drives the styling system. State management is split between Zustand (client state: auth, UI) and TanStack React Query (server state: API data, caching). The frontend communicates exclusively with the backend REST API using Axios.</p>

  <h4>Tier 2 – Application Layer (Backend)</h4>
  <p>The backend is a Node.js + Express.js 5 REST API written in TypeScript. It is organized into domain modules (auth, materials, user, chatbot, code, admin, ai, ocr), each with its own router, controller, and service layer. Firebase Admin SDK validates authentication tokens on every protected request. A separate background worker process (BullMQ consumer) handles asynchronous material processing jobs from a Redis queue.</p>

  <h4>Tier 3 – Data Layer</h4>
  <p>The data layer comprises three distinct storage systems:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>MongoDB Atlas:</strong> Primary document database storing Material records with full metadata, extracted text, and page structures.</li>
    <li><strong>Firebase Firestore:</strong> NoSQL cloud database for User profiles, authentication records, and session data.</li>
    <li><strong>Pinecone:</strong> Managed vector database storing dense embeddings of material page content for semantic similarity search.</li>
    <li><strong>Cloudinary:</strong> CDN-backed cloud object storage for uploaded PDF files and generated thumbnails.</li>
    <li><strong>Redis:</strong> In-memory store backing the BullMQ job queue and caching layer.</li>
  </ul>

