  <h3>3.1.4 Authentication Flow</h3>
  <p>Authentication follows a Firebase-JWT hybrid model:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>User initiates Google Sign-In on the frontend via Firebase Client SDK.</li>
    <li>Firebase OAuth 2.0 flow completes; Firebase issues a short-lived ID Token (1 hour expiry).</li>
    <li>Frontend stores the token in memory (Zustand) and attaches it as <code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;</code> on every API request.</li>
    <li>Backend middleware <code>verifyFirebaseToken</code> calls Firebase Admin SDK to verify and decode the token.</li>
    <li>Decoded <code>firebaseUid</code> is used to load the user profile from Firestore.</li>
    <li>Role-based middleware (<code>requireAdmin</code>, <code>requireAppUser</code>) enforces access control on protected routes.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>3.1.5 Material Processing Pipeline</h3>
  <p>When a user uploads a PDF, the following asynchronous pipeline executes:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Upload:</strong> Multer middleware receives the file; it is uploaded to Cloudinary and a Material document is created in MongoDB with status: "processing".</li>
    <li><strong>Queue:</strong> A job is enqueued to BullMQ (backed by Redis) with the material ID.</li>
    <li><strong>OCR:</strong> Worker fetches the PDF from Cloudinary, sends pages to NVIDIA PaddleOCR API, and receives structured text per page.</li>
    <li><strong>Embedding:</strong> Extracted text is chunked per page; Google Generative AI embedding model generates dense vectors for each chunk.</li>
    <li><strong>Indexing:</strong> Vectors are upserted to Pinecone with material ID and page metadata as payload.</li>
    <li><strong>Update:</strong> MongoDB Material document is updated with extracted page text and status: "done". Frontend polls <code>/materials/status/:id</code> to reflect completion.</li>
  </ol>

