  <h2>3.3 Database Design</h2>

  <h3>3.3.1 MongoDB – Material Collection Schema</h3>
  <p><strong>Table 3.1: Material Schema</strong></p>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    <tr><td>_id</td><td>ObjectId</td><td>Auto</td><td>MongoDB primary key</td></tr>
    <tr><td>title</td><td>String</td><td>Yes</td><td>Material title</td></tr>
    <tr><td>description</td><td>String</td><td>No</td><td>Optional description</td></tr>
    <tr><td>year</td><td>String</td><td>Yes</td><td>Academic year (e.g., "2023")</td></tr>
    <tr><td>fileUrl</td><td>String</td><td>Yes</td><td>Cloudinary secure URL</td></tr>
    <tr><td>fileName</td><td>String</td><td>Yes</td><td>Original file name</td></tr>
    <tr><td>fileType</td><td>String</td><td>Yes</td><td>MIME type (application/pdf)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>fileSize</td><td>Number</td><td>Yes</td><td>File size in bytes</td></tr>
    <tr><td>cloudinaryPublicId</td><td>String</td><td>Yes</td><td>Cloudinary asset ID for deletion</td></tr>
    <tr><td>uploaderId</td><td>String</td><td>Yes</td><td>Firebase UID of uploader</td></tr>
    <tr><td>uploaderName</td><td>String</td><td>No</td><td>Display name of uploader</td></tr>
    <tr><td>subject</td><td>String</td><td>No</td><td>Subject name</td></tr>
    <tr><td>subjectCode</td><td>String</td><td>No</td><td>Subject code (e.g., "IT804A")</td></tr>
    <tr><td>branch</td><td>String</td><td>No</td><td>Branch (e.g., "IT", "CS")</td></tr>
    <tr><td>semester</td><td>Number</td><td>No</td><td>Semester number (1–8)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>downloads</td><td>Number</td><td>Default: 0</td><td>Download count</td></tr>
    <tr><td>status</td><td>Enum</td><td>Default: "processing"</td><td>processing | done | failed</td></tr>
    <tr><td>pages</td><td>Array</td><td>No</td><td>Array of { pageNumber, rawText, structured }</td></tr>
    <tr><td>structuredData</td><td>Object</td><td>No</td><td>Top-level structured metadata</td></tr>
    <tr><td>createdAt</td><td>Date</td><td>Auto</td><td>Mongoose timestamp</td></tr>
    <tr><td>updatedAt</td><td>Date</td><td>Auto</td><td>Mongoose timestamp</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h3>3.3.2 Firebase Firestore – User Document Schema</h3>
  <p><strong>Table 3.2: User Schema</strong></p>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    <tr><td>id</td><td>String</td><td>Firestore document ID</td></tr>
    <tr><td>firebaseUid</td><td>String</td><td>Firebase Authentication UID</td></tr>
    <tr><td>email</td><td>String</td><td>User email from Google account</td></tr>
    <tr><td>displayName</td><td>String</td><td>Google display name</td></tr>
    <tr><td>photoURL</td><td>String</td><td>Google profile photo URL</td></tr>
    <tr><td>role</td><td>Enum</td><td>student | teacher | admin</td></tr>
    <tr><td>isVerified</td><td>Boolean</td><td>Admin-verified (for teachers)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>isProfileComplete</td><td>Boolean</td><td>Profile setup completion flag</td></tr>
    <tr><td>studentProfile</td><td>Object</td><td>{ fullName, semester, branch, college, enrollmentNumber }</td></tr>
    <tr><td>teacherProfile</td><td>Object</td><td>{ fullName }</td></tr>
    <tr><td>bookmarkedMaterialIds</td><td>String[]</td><td>Array of bookmarked material ObjectIds</td></tr>
    <tr><td>createdAt</td><td>Timestamp</td><td>Firestore server timestamp</td></tr>
    <tr><td>updatedAt</td><td>Timestamp</td><td>Firestore server timestamp</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h3>3.3.3 Pinecone – Vector Index Schema</h3>
  <p>Each vector record in Pinecone contains:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>id:</strong> Composite key — <code>{materialId}_page_{pageNumber}</code></li>
    <li><strong>values:</strong> Dense float32 embedding vector (768/1536 dimensions depending on model)</li>
    <li><strong>metadata:</strong> { materialId, pageNumber, subject, branch, semester }</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Queries against Pinecone use a search embedding generated from the user's query, with metadata filters for branch/semester to scope results.</p>
</div>

<!-- ===== CHAPTER 4: IMPLEMENTATION ===== -->
<div class="page-break">
  <h1>CHAPTER 4<br/>IMPLEMENTATION</h1>

  <h2>4.1 Algorithm &amp; Methodology</h2>

  <h3>4.1.1 RAG-Based Document Q&amp;A Algorithm</h3>
  <p>Study Share implements a lightweight Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline for document-specific question answering:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Indexing Phase (at upload time):</strong>
      <ol type="a">
        <li>PDF is converted to images (pdf2pic) and sent to NVIDIA PaddleOCR for text extraction.</li>
        <li>Per-page text is chunked into manageable segments.</li>
        <li>Google Generative AI <code>text-embedding-004</code> model generates a dense vector per chunk.</li>
        <li>Vectors are upserted to Pinecone with page and material metadata.</li>
      </ol>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Query Phase (at chat time):</strong>
      <ol type="a">
        <li>User's question text is embedded using the same model.</li>
        <li>Pinecone ANN query returns top-k most similar page chunks filtered by material ID.</li>
        <li>Retrieved chunk texts are assembled as context.</li>
        <li>Gemini API is prompted with: System role + retrieved context + conversation history + user question.</li>
        <li>Gemini's response is streamed back and rendered in Markdown in the frontend chat panel.</li>
      </ol>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h3>4.1.2 Background Job Processing Algorithm</h3>
  <p>The BullMQ job queue implements an exponential backoff retry strategy:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Max Retries:</strong> 3 attempts per job</li>
    <li><strong>Backoff:</strong> Exponential (2s, 4s, 8s delays)</li>
    <li><strong>On Failure:</strong> Material status updated to "failed"; error logged</li>
    <li><strong>Concurrency:</strong> Worker configured for 5 concurrent jobs</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4.1.3 Semantic Search Algorithm</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>User submits a search query string.</li>
    <li>Backend generates an embedding vector for the query.</li>
    <li>Pinecone top-k query (k=10) retrieves most semantically similar material page vectors.</li>
    <li>Distinct material IDs from results are used to fetch full Material documents from MongoDB.</li>
    <li>Results are ranked by similarity score and returned to the frontend.</li>
    <li>Fallback: If Pinecone returns fewer than 3 results, MongoDB text index search supplements results.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>4.2 Module Descriptions</h2>

  <h3>4.2.1 Authentication Module (modules/auth)</h3>
  <p>Handles user registration and session management. Key responsibilities:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Receives Firebase ID token; calls Firebase Admin SDK to verify and decode user identity.</li>
    <li>Checks Firestore for existing user record; creates new record for first-time users.</li>
    <li>Manages the student and teacher registration forms with profile completion tracking.</li>
    <li>Implements admin-only endpoint for teacher verification workflow.</li>
    <li>Provides <code>verifyFirebaseToken</code> middleware used across all protected routes.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4.2.2 Materials Module (modules/materials)</h3>
  <p>The core business module. Key responsibilities:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Upload Controller:</strong> Handles multipart form data via Multer; uploads to Cloudinary; creates MongoDB Material document; enqueues processing job.</li>
    <li><strong>Browse/Filter Controller:</strong> Queries MongoDB with optional filters (branch, semester, subject, year, search). Uses MongoDB text index for keyword search.</li>
    <li><strong>PDF Viewer API:</strong> Returns signed Cloudinary URLs for inline viewing; supports page-level text retrieval.</li>
    <li><strong>Chat Controller:</strong> Implements the RAG Q&amp;A pipeline per document.</li>
    <li><strong>Status Controller:</strong> Polls and returns current processing status for a material.</li>
    <li><strong>Download Controller:</strong> Increments download counter atomically via MongoDB <code>$inc</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4.2.3 OCR Module (modules/ocr)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Fetches PDF from Cloudinary using URL.</li>
    <li>Converts PDF pages to images using pdf2pic and Canvas.</li>
    <li>Sends images to NVIDIA Baidu PaddleOCR API for layout-aware text extraction.</li>
    <li>Returns structured per-page text array to the materials processing pipeline.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4.2.4 AI Module (modules/ai)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Wraps Google Generative AI SDK (<code>@google/genai</code>) for embedding generation and text generation.</li>
    <li>Provides a unified <code>generateEmbedding(text)</code> function used by both indexing and query pipelines.</li>
    <li>Manages Pinecone client initialization and provides <code>upsertVectors()</code> and <code>queryVectors()</code> utility functions.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4.2.5 Chatbot Module (modules/chatbot)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Manages general-purpose AI chat sessions stored in Firestore.</li>
    <li>Sessions are user-scoped with persistent message history.</li>
    <li>Each message exchange is appended to the session document; history is passed as context to Gemini on each turn.</li>
    <li>Session deletion cascades to all associated messages.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4.2.6 Code Execution Module (modules/code)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Accepts <code>{ code, language }</code> payload from the frontend Monaco Editor.</li>
    <li>Translates language to Judge0 language ID.</li>
    <li>Submits code to Judge0 API for sandboxed execution with a 10-second timeout.</li>
    <li>Returns stdout, stderr, and status to the frontend.</li>
    <li>Frontend also provides OneCompiler iframe as an alternative embedded editor.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4.2.7 Admin Module (modules/admin)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Aggregates platform statistics: total users, total materials, downloads, pending teacher verifications.</li>
    <li>Provides CRUD operations over all users (view, search, delete) restricted to admin role.</li>
    <li>Provides material listing and deletion for content moderation.</li>
    <li>Teacher verification endpoint triggers <code>isVerified: true</code> update on Firestore user document.</li>
  </ul>

