<!-- ===== CHAPTER 5: TESTING ===== -->
<div class="page-break">
  <h1>CHAPTER 5<br/>TESTING &amp; RESULTS</h1>

  <h2>5.1 Testing Strategy</h2>
  <p>The testing strategy for Study Share encompasses multiple levels of testing to ensure functional correctness, security, performance, and usability across all supported devices and roles.</p>

  <h3>5.1.1 Testing Levels</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Unit Testing:</strong> Individual functions and utility methods (embedding generation, OCR parsing, API response formatters) tested in isolation.</li>
    <li><strong>Integration Testing:</strong> API endpoint testing using REST client (Postman/Insomnia) verifying request-response cycles, authentication enforcement, and database state changes.</li>
    <li><strong>System Testing:</strong> End-to-end functional testing covering full user workflows from login to material Q&amp;A.</li>
    <li><strong>Acceptance Testing:</strong> User acceptance testing (UAT) conducted with student volunteers to validate usability and feature completeness.</li>
    <li><strong>Security Testing:</strong> Attempted unauthorized access to protected endpoints; SQL/NoSQL injection testing; token expiry handling verification.</li>
    <li><strong>Responsive Testing:</strong> Cross-device testing on iOS Safari, Android Chrome, and desktop browsers at multiple viewport sizes.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5.2 Test Cases &amp; Validation</h2>

  <h3>5.2.1 Authentication Module Test Cases</h3>
